node.text:
Stop waiting on a breakthrough and start evolving into it. Develop yourself so much that you can no longer sit in comfort zones because you’ve proved to yourself how much you actually are capable of growing through. Surrender to the fact that perfection doesn’t exist and you WILL fall many times. Without those errors, you couldn’t gain the strength or lessons needed for the next growth phase in your life. Keep exploring your potential, you have ONE life to live! 💯 
Wearing @evolvegear New Reflective Sweatshirt Releasing March 4!!!

The only New Years resolution you need to make this next year is to live your life with less fear and on your own terms. Stop being afraid of making mistakes and being judged. Change is constant; you’re either moving with it or getting left behind. The choice is YOURS. 
-
#EVOLVENATION

node.text: Truthfully speaking, I did not physically train or prepare for this 5 mile challenge. In fact, it was my first 5 mile race ever and having to navigate ourselves to the destination made it even more challenging. I went into this race with the intent of seeing just how far my mind could push my body. The title for coming in first place isn’t where the value sits for me. Conquering the mental battle and proving to myself that I am capable of anything is the true victory. Blessed and ready to chase bigger goals. Thank you for the opportunity and experience @underarmour @uarunning #UAHOVR #UAPartner

Today’s burnout consisted of speed, strength and reactive work with @coach_yassin 
15 strokes on the ski machine ➡️ combos on the mitts ➡️ 5 30 lb ball slams ➡️ 30 lb DB snatches + push-up ➡️ 10 Knees to the body 
Hit this for 3-5 rounds with no rest for a killer strength conditioning workout. 
Save this post and tag a friend who would do this workout with you 👊🏽 Wearing: @womensbestwear 
Sneakers: @rovuxfootwear

node.text:
Burn fat and save time, it’s a win-win. 
LIKE | SAVE | SHARE 🔥 
5-10 rounds 
20 seconds cycling sprint (high resistance) 
10 plyo pushups 
10 hanging alternating cross-knee raises 
10 hanging oblique knee raises 
Rest 30-60 seconds in between each round 
It’s a short workout, put in your all and get the most out of it! 
Share with a friend and let me know if you want more videos like this!

node.text:
LIKE | SAVE | SHARE 🔥
A big misconception people have with training core is that they treat it as a single muscle rather than a muscle group. Sit ups or even planks alone will not cut it. The best way to define and strengthen the entirety of your core is by working every muscle in the core (Rectus abs, external/internal obliques, transverse abs, etc). These 3 exercises cover them all. Slow and controlled is my preference. 
Like/Comment if you want more videos like this!🦁 ⬇️

node.text:
I believe we often forget that EVEN if life is unfair, it’s still up to us to make the best out of it (because we deserve it). But instead, some will completely throw away their goals with the belief that this is how to get back at life but it’s you, that you’re hurting. At the end of the day, you are the common denominator of everything in your life. It’s easy to give up. It’s easy to blame others and circumstances. It’s easy to downgrade your standards so you’re ok with what you didn’t achieve. You could have chose to push through the challenges and discover a different outcome. Don’t live in the “could of” mentality. Do it now and keep going. The lessons you learn and the character you develop on the way up are the biggest rewards. Rise up, Evolvers 🕊

Tag someone who needs to hear this 🗣💯 
Wearing @evolvegear

node.text:
Sometimes happiness looks like staying at home, minding your own business and saying no to people so you can focus on you. That’s usually where I am. But when my soul needs more - I explore. Both the world and within myself. I change routine, I adapt to my new environment and I keep evolving. Its not always easy but it’s essential for self-development - in fitness and life. Growth in general requires change. Go to new places, meet new people, experience new things and gain new perspectives! Once you stop learning, you stop growing. EXPLORE THE UNKNOWN, EVOLVERS 🌍 🕊🔝 

🏷 Save this talk & Share it with someone who needs it! ❤️‍🔥 

#EvolveNation 
📍 @titanic_deluxe_bodrum 
Wearing: @womensbestwear
